	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64483175">People might be scared of nuclear, but coal mining leads to more fatalities: <span class="substr"> </span><a href="https://wwwn.cdc.gov/NIOSH-Mining/MMWC/Fatality/NumberAndRate?StartYear=1983&amp;EndYear=2022&amp;SelectedOperatorType=0&amp;SelectedMineType=1&amp;SelectedCommodity=1" title="cdc.gov" rel="nofollow">https://wwwn.cdc.gov/NIOSH-Min...</a> [cdc.gov]

<br>
And these are direct worker deaths, not some seagull getting lung cancer.
<br>
<a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_nuclear_and_radiation_accidents_by_death_toll" title="wikipedia.org" rel="nofollow">https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wik...</a> [wikipedia.org]
<br>
Nuclear has a much better track record, even when comparing worldwide nuclear to just US coal, which is a comparison tilted against nuclear.
People who are afraid of nuclear because of that reactor in Japan that failed in a generally safe manner almost 15 years ago have a lot more to be s</div>
	</div>

